==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rebec
<hw>Re"bec</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧"b⟦ecr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
It. <ets>ribeca</ets>, <ets>ribeba</ets>, fr. Ar. <ets>rab⟦amac⟧b</ets>
a musical instrument of a round form.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An instrument formerly used which somewhat
resembled the violin, having three strings, and being played with a
bow.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>rebeck</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He turn'd his <qex>rebec</qex> to a mournful note.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A contemptuous term applied to an old woman.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rebel</ent>⟦br⟧
